<P>
GUNMAN KILLS JAPANESE TEEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Jose police searched for a gunman who killed a 16-year-old Japanese 
exchange student. Ai Toyoshima, who arrived in this country just two months 
ago, died from a gunshot wound to the chest by an unidentified assailant. The 
wounded girl was found by a passer-by in a field behind an elementary school. 
Barely alive, Toyoshima was taken to a hospital, where before she died, she 
described her assailant to a police officer who speaks Japanese. She died at 6 
a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
