<TEXT>
<P>
Seven people were injured, three of them critically, in a traffic accident on 
the southbound San Diego Freeway in San Juan Capistrano. Two of the victims 
were children, Orange County Fire Department dispatcher Leo Schneider said. The 
accident, which involved a pickup that flipped over, occurred south of Junipero 
Serra Road and was reported about 8:35 a.m. Sunday, he said. 
</P>
