<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Korean patrol boats rescued 78 Vietnamese refugees who set their boat on 
fire and jumped into the sea after they were refused permission to land, the 
South Korean news agency Yonhap said. The patrol boats were escorting the 
refugee vessel out to international waters when the 30-ton boat suddenly burst 
into flames and sank off the southern island of Cheju, Yonhap quoted naval 
police as saying. It was not immediately clear whether the Seoul government 
would allow the "boat people" to settle in South Korea. 
</P>
