<P>
ARAB SHOOTS ISRAELI OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Israeli army officer in the occupied Gaza Strip was shot and wounded when an 
Arab gunman opened fire from a passing car. An Arab newspaper vendor was killed 
in the gunfire, an army spokesman said. The attack marked a rare use of 
firearms against the Israeli army in the 18-month-old Arab uprising. In the 
West Bank, Israeli troops shot and killed two Arab youths in separate 
incidents, and an Israeli from the settlement of Ariel was found stabbed to 
death. The Israeli Cabinet, meanwhile, outlawed three fundamentalist Muslim 
groups -- the Islamic Resistance Movement, Hezbollah (Party of God) and Islamic 
Jihad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
