<P>
DRAIN, RECREATION PLANS FOR DEER CANYON STUDIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Representatives from the city engineer's office will attend a special meeting 
to discuss proposed improvements to Deer Canyon on June 28, from 7 to 10 p.m. 
at Canyon Hills Library, 400 Scout Trail. 
</P>
<P>
Topics will include information on a proposed storm drain and recreational 
improvements to Deer Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting is sponsored by the city Parks, Recreation and Community Services 
Department. For information, contact Chris Jarvi, the department's director, at 
999-5160. 
