<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
WORK ON WARNER AVENUE TO SLOW, DETOUR TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Warner Avenue between Euclid Street and the Santa Ana River is undergoing a 
major reconstruction that will cause traffic slowdowns and detours in the area 
through September. 
</P>
<P>
In announcing the $850,000 project, the city of Fountain Valley urged residents 
and businesses to seek alternate routes. 
</P>
<P>
The project will primarily affect two residential neighborhoods. One is bounded 
by Euclid Street, Warner Avenue, Newhope Street and the Warner Flood Control 
Channel. The other is bounded by Newhope, Warner, the Santa Ana River, Harbor 
Boulevard and Quartz Street. 
</P>
<P>
Those who normally use Warner to enter and exit their neighborhoods will have 
to use Euclid and Newhope streets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
