<P>
Beat Breu regained the overall lead in the Tour of Switzerland by winning the 
road cycling race's sixth stage, a 4.7-mile uphill time trial to Heitersberg, 
Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, West Germany's Remig Stumpf was a surprise winner in a mass 
arrival at the finish of the fifth stage, a 49-mile ride from Bad Zurzach to 
Baden. 
</P>
<P>
Breu, a Swiss, was eight seconds ahead ahead of countryman Thomas Wegmueller in 
the subsequent race over a 685-foot vertical rise. Breu, with a total time of 
20 hours 8 minutes 49 seconds, reclaimed the overall leader's yellow jersey 
from Stephan Joho of Switzerland, who led for two days. 
