<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIGG, TINLEY FINISH 1-2 IN TRIATHLON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SHIZUOKA, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Pigg led an American sweep of the top two places in the men's competition 
Sunday while compatriot Erin Baker took the women's title in the Japan 
Triathlon Series Nippondaira. 
</P>
<P>
Pigg, the 1987-88 U.S. champion, swam .93 miles in 20 minutes 11 seconds, 
bicycled 24.8 miles in 52:52 seconds, and ran 6.2 miles in 34 minutes for a 
total time of 1 hour 48 minutes 34 seconds, including transit time, to win the 
men's race. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Tinley finished second with a total time of 1:51:43, followed by Ronnie 
Hansen of Denmark in 1:53:13. 
</P>
<P>
Baker's winning time was 2:01:14, followed by Canadian Julia Deck in 2:02:50. 
The third-place finisher was Kirsten Hansen in 2:06:26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
