<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUN PLAY KILLS 3RD CHILD; NEW LAW WEIGHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAMPA, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 4-year-old who shot himself while playing with a gun a week ago has become 
the third Florida child to die in a recent spate of accidents involving 
handguns kept in the home. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, Silvio Claud Pierre, died Saturday night in Tampa General Hospital 
after undergoing seven hours of surgery. 
</P>
<P>
Florida legislators this week are to consider a bill that would make it a 
misdemeanor to leave a firearm in a place accessible to a child. If a child 
died or was permanently disfigured in a case involving negligence, the offense 
would be a felony with a maximum five-year prison term. 
</P>
</TEXT>
