<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
680 Workers Volunteer to Leave Xerox: Xerox Corp. said 680 employees nationwide 
have joined a voluntary job cut program announced in March. Xerox spokesman 
John Rasor said the voluntary reductions won't guarantee against future layoffs 
but the company had predicted that only 250 to 350 would take advantage of the 
program. In January, Xerox announced a $275-million streamlining program that 
would cut 2,000 jobs. Company officials it had not been decided if the rest of 
the job cuts would come through layoffs or voluntary retirements and 
resignations. The company said the market for cheaper and medium-priced 
electronic typewriters has shrunk much faster than expected, leaving the 
industry with excess capacity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
XEROX CORP; LAYOFFS; CORPORATE RESTRUCTURING; OFFICE EQUIPMENT 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061989-0079 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 72241 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 19, 1989, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
