<P>
Business; Part 4; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
72 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Growers Consider Giving Apples Away: As sales of Washington apples hit their 
lowest point of an Alar-plagued year, some growers are considering giving away 
fruit to the poor as a way to reduce supplies and raise prices. One proposal 
includes taking a truckload of Washington apples to New York City and giving 
them away to show how desperate the situation is, said Jim Clements, president 
of the Washington Assn. of Apple Growers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
