<P>
Illinois Offers $33 Million to Sears: Illinois has offered $33 million to 
Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co. to keep its retail headquarters in the state it has 
called home for more than 100 years. Sears has said it will announce by the end 
of the month whether its 6,000-employee Merchandise Group will remain in 
Illinois. Speculation for a new site has focused on an area west of Chicago, 
Dallas, and Raleigh and Charlotte, N.C. The Merchandise Group, which has a $411 
million annual payroll and produces about $19.4 million a year in state and 
local taxes, is being moved from Sears Tower to cut costs; the company is also 
selling the skyscraper. Gov. James R. Thompson signed legislation earmarking 
$33 million to Sears' incentive package. The money could be used for land, site 
improvements or infrastructure at any Illinois site. Chicago already has 
offered unspecified incentives to Sears. 
