<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC STORM WEAKENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MIAMI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tropical Storm Barbara lost much of its punch today as it moved into the colder 
waters of the Pacific, about 450 miles west southwest of the southern tip of 
Baja California, the National Hurricane Center said. 
</P>
<P>
Barbara, the first hurricane of the season, was downgraded to a tropical storm 
on Sunday, after its sustained winds fell below 74 m.p.h. The storm formed 
Thursday and reached hurricane strength Saturday. 
</P>
