THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
CARDINAL'S POWER REPLACES MCGEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The St. Louis Cardinals today reinstated right-handed pitcher Ted Power to 
replace outfielder Willie McGee, who was retroactively placed on the 21-day 
disabled list with a sprained left wrist. 
</P>
<P>
The Cardinals also announced that team doctor Stan London put McGee's wrist in 
a cast Tuesday. London said the cast would help immobilize the wrist. 
</P>
<P>
McGee last appeared in a game June 6. His placement on the disabled list is 
retroactive to June 7. 
</P>
<P>
Power, 34, comes off the 21-day disabled list. He suffered a pulled left 
rib-cage muscle May 17 at Houston. 
</P>
