<HEADLINE>
<P>
AQUINO VOWS FIGHT ON 'SHAMELESS CORRUPTION' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philippine President Corazon Aquino today admitted government corruption has 
returned on a shameless scale under her presidency and said she will lead a 
major campaign to stamp it out no matter who gets hurt. 
</P>
<P>
Aquino also lashed out at her critics, calling them "thieves" who have no right 
to preach to her about honesty because they plundered the economy when they 
were in power. 
</P>
<P>
She said the anti-corruption campaign "must spare no one," neither friends who 
helped bring her to power nor her political enemies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
